HEADWORD: Rheostat
<hw>Rhe"o*stat</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧"⟦osl⟧*st⟦acr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>"rei^n</grk> + <grk>stato`s</grk> standing still.]</ety>
<fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A contrivance for adjusting or regulating the
strength of electrical currents, operating usually by the intercalation
of resistance which can be varied at will.</def> <au>Wheatstone.</au>
--<wordforms><wf>Rhe`o*stat"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rheotome</ent>⟦br⟧
